review_blob: Recommended by the bartender at the Old Bank, this is a fantastic Finnish porter. Not too heavy in any way, nice earthy/ mineral flavors. This was a smooth drinking and clean finishing beer. The end of the glass did not get too bitter. For a stronger beer, none of the alcohol comes through. Bottled version held up as well, easily just as good.

Not a bad Pilsner, nice pale yellow color and white head. Light aroma with some malts and hops. Nice pilsener taste with a clean finish, but a little sweet and Id like the hops to come through more. Easy to drink.
